1
00:00:01,211 --> 00:00:26,477
Okay, we can begin.

2
00:00:32,869 --> 00:00:59,383
Namo Tassa Bhagavato Arahato Sambha Sambhodasa Namo Tassa Bhagavato Arahato Sambha Sambhodasa

3
00:01:00,375 --> 00:01:24,325
Namo Tassa Bhagavato Arahato Sambha Sambuddhasa Bodhansaranam Gacchami Damansaranam Gacchami Sangamsaranam Gacchami

4
00:01:25,081 --> 00:01:51,644
Tuthi Ampi Bodham Saranam Gacchami Tuthi Ampi Damang Saranam Gacchami Tuthi Ampi Sangam Saranam Gacchami Tuthi Ampi Bodham Saranam Gacchami

5
00:01:52,334 --> 00:02:21,074
Tatyampi Damang Saranang Gacchami Tatyampi Sandang Saranang Gacchami Panatipata Velamani Sikapadan Samadhi Ami Adhinadana Velamani

6
00:02:21,342 --> 00:02:44,953
Sikapada Samadhi Ami Kamesumi Cacera Velamani Sikapada Samadhi Ami Musawadda Velamani Sikapada Samadhi Ami

7
00:02:45,203 --> 00:03:10,247
So we can begin our sitting.

8
00:03:11,068 --> 00:03:14,551
So make sure you are comfortable, feeling comfortable.

9
00:03:18,937 --> 00:03:20,378
Settling on the breath.

10
00:03:23,644 --> 00:03:36,563
We can begin our sitting with these evening contemplations, which the Buddha says are there to make us more enthusiastic, to give us some real purpose as to why we're practicing.

11
00:03:39,729 --> 00:03:45,197
So just repeating these phrases to ourselves.

12
00:03:54,239 --> 00:04:21,377
this body is subject to disease this body is of a nature to fall ill this body has not gone beyond sickness this body is subject to aging

13
00:04:26,182 --> 00:04:53,963
This body has not gone beyond ageing This body is now in a process of ageing This body is subject to death This body has not gone beyond death

14
00:04:58,987 --> 00:05:00,389
This body will die.

15
00:05:00,410 --> 00:05:14,326
There is the unborn, undying, uncreated, uncompounded.

16
00:05:20,392 --> 00:05:21,334
The unconditioned.

17
00:05:26,612 --> 00:05:29,055
True refuge, harbour and home.

18
00:05:34,603 --> 00:05:37,026
Perfect peace and contentment.

19
00:05:43,755 --> 00:05:49,362
Those who are mindful are in the presence, in the vicinity of Nibbana.

20
00:40:56,137 --> 00:41:04,630
So a moment's reflection, just looking back at the time, picking up on something, working with tiredness.

21
00:41:06,853 --> 00:41:07,994
Was it restlessness?

22
00:41:08,054 --> 00:41:09,737
Was some emotional stuff came up?

23
00:41:10,038 --> 00:41:10,960
Wandering mind?

24
00:41:11,500 --> 00:41:12,541
How did you deal with it?

25
00:41:28,030 --> 00:41:33,739
Don't forget, if you thought you were rather skillful, we should congratulate ourselves.

26
00:41:33,820 --> 00:41:37,126
If we thought we could have been more skillful, we should encourage ourselves.

27
00:41:46,983 --> 00:41:52,653
And we can make a resolution, either specific or general or both.

28
00:42:05,273 --> 00:42:11,702
So we can just begin our contemplations always beginning with compassion.

29
00:42:12,742 --> 00:42:18,572
So again, it's a case of turning this goodwill compassion towards ourselves.

30
00:42:19,813 --> 00:42:33,913
And if we find that difficult, just to put our hands over our hearts and just consider some of the things that we've done to ourselves, which has caused harm, physical, mental, emotional,

31
00:42:36,981 --> 00:42:53,673
something comes up for you and just allow yourself to forgive yourself

32
00:43:02,581 --> 00:43:11,050
Then just turning that compassion towards our own hearts, speaking gently into the heart.

33
00:43:12,731 --> 00:43:15,394
May I be free of physical pain.

34
00:43:20,400 --> 00:43:23,224
May I be free of mental distress.

35
00:43:29,391 --> 00:43:32,554
May I be free of all my sufferings.

36
00:43:53,829 --> 00:43:58,556
We can bring to mind now somebody whom we know is not having a good time one way or the other.

37
00:44:05,907 --> 00:44:10,514
And as you picture them in your mind's eye, just drive your goodwill towards them.

38
00:44:13,458 --> 00:44:15,481
May you be free of physical pain.

39
00:44:20,246 --> 00:44:22,791
May you be free of mental distress.

40
00:44:27,918 --> 00:44:30,942
May you be liberated of all your sufferings.

41
00:44:55,559 --> 00:45:01,103
And we can bring to mind all those at this moment who are sick and or suffering from mental illness.

42
00:45:02,885 --> 00:45:09,472
People in the process of dying and those who have died and left grieving family, relatives and friends.

43
00:45:11,954 --> 00:45:14,876
People going hungry, homeless and destitute.

44
00:45:17,739 --> 00:45:22,443
Those having to deal with severe personal and interpersonal difficulties.

45
00:45:25,934 --> 00:45:54,827
all those caught up in wars and repressive regimes those being tortured and there are those suffering from natural disasters and climate crisis all the sentient beings have been cruelly treated and unnecessarily slaughtered and all who find life

46
00:45:55,110 --> 00:45:55,831
meaningless.

47
00:46:00,579 --> 00:46:02,621
May you be free of physical pain.

48
00:46:07,550 --> 00:46:09,713
May you be free of mental distress.

49
00:46:16,362 --> 00:46:19,447
May you be liberated of all your sufferings.

50
00:46:42,411 --> 00:46:47,717
And we can radiate this goodwill, compassion to all beings in all directions.

51
00:46:49,018 --> 00:46:52,121
May all beings be free of physical pain.

52
00:46:57,146 --> 00:47:00,070
May all beings be free of mental distress.

53
00:47:05,775 --> 00:47:09,498
May all beings be liberated of all their sufferings.

54
00:47:34,657 --> 00:47:45,068
Bring to mind now some moments during the day when you've experienced love or peace, joy, some level of happiness.

55
00:47:45,268 --> 00:47:46,449
Just bring it to mind.

56
00:47:50,594 --> 00:47:51,715
Be grateful for it.

57
00:48:00,884 --> 00:48:03,347
Then just let's wish ourselves

58
00:48:04,222 --> 00:48:08,992
This joyfulness, again speaking joyfully into the heart.

59
00:48:10,094 --> 00:48:11,396
May I be joyful.

60
00:48:14,844 --> 00:48:16,628
May my joyfulness increase.

61
00:48:22,039 --> 00:48:24,525
May I experience the bliss of Nirvana.

62
00:48:54,019 --> 00:48:58,146
We can bring to mind now somebody whom we know has cause to be joyful.

63
00:49:05,255 --> 00:49:11,304
As you picture them in your mind's eye, drive your goodwill joy towards them.

64
00:49:14,188 --> 00:49:15,429
May you be joyful.

65
00:49:19,014 --> 00:49:20,938
May your joyfulness increase.

66
00:49:25,862 --> 00:49:54,317
may you experience the bliss of nibbana and there are people at this moment who are happy and content with their lives

67
00:49:55,411 --> 00:50:10,744
enjoying the warmth of friendship, the support of friendship, enjoying the delights of art and nature, enjoying the work they do, finding it meaningful, fruitful.

68
00:50:12,005 --> 00:50:16,150
And there's also the fruitfulness of those practicing spiritually.

69
00:50:16,210 --> 00:50:23,376
And there are those who are joyful because they rejoice in the joy of others.

70
00:50:28,672 --> 00:50:30,074
May they be joyful.

71
00:50:34,804 --> 00:50:36,528
May their joyfulness increase.

72
00:50:41,760 --> 00:50:44,706
May they experience the bliss of Nirvana.

73
00:51:07,670 --> 00:51:12,077
and radiating this joy to all beings in all directions.

74
00:51:13,378 --> 00:51:15,681
May all beings be joyful.

75
00:51:21,550 --> 00:51:23,353
May their joyfulness increase.

76
00:51:29,762 --> 00:51:35,431
May they experience, may all beings experience the bliss of Nirvana.

77
00:52:06,664 --> 00:52:10,630
I shall read again the Discourse on Goodwill, Metta.

78
00:52:12,634 --> 00:52:17,721
If you are wise and want to reach the state of peace, you should behave like this.

79
00:52:19,063 --> 00:52:23,228
You should be upright, responsible, gentle and humble.

80
00:52:23,248 --> 00:52:28,577
You should be easily contented and need only a few things.

81
00:52:30,298 --> 00:52:32,181
You should not always be busy.

82
00:52:32,222 --> 00:52:35,726
You should have the right sort of work.

83
00:52:37,360 --> 00:52:41,666
Your senses should be guarded and you should be modest.

84
00:52:43,429 --> 00:52:52,681
You should not be exclusively attached to only a few people and you should not do the slightest thing that a wise person would blame you for.

85
00:52:54,824 --> 00:53:07,181
You should always be thinking, may all beings be happy, whatever living beings they are, be they weak or small, big or small, large or slender,

86
00:53:07,583 --> 00:53:14,572
living nearby or far away, those who've already been born and those who have yet to be born.

87
00:53:15,353 --> 00:53:18,237
May all beings, without exception, be happy.

88
00:53:20,440 --> 00:53:26,148
You should not tell lies to each other and do not think anyone anywhere is of no value.

89
00:53:27,730 --> 00:53:35,219
Do not wish harm to anyone, not even when you're angry, just as a mother would protect her only child.

90
00:53:36,101 --> 00:53:37,302
So you should let that

91
00:53:37,637 --> 00:53:40,300
the warmth of your heart go out to all beings.

92
00:53:41,141 --> 00:53:50,309
Let your thoughts of love go through the whole world, above and below, without any fear, with no ill will and no hatred.

93
00:53:52,132 --> 00:54:00,480
Whether you are standing, walking, sitting or lying down, so long as you are awake, you should develop this mindfulness.

94
00:54:01,902 --> 00:54:04,083
This, they say, is the noblest way to live.

95
00:54:05,278 --> 00:54:21,315
And if you do not fall into unskillful ways, but live well and develop insight and are no longer attached to all the desires of the senses, then truly you'll never need to be reborn into this world again.

96
00:54:21,335 --> 00:54:24,398
So I'll chant the discourse.

97
00:54:25,077 --> 00:54:28,442
And if you wish, those of you who know it, of course, can chant with me.

98
00:54:29,202 --> 00:54:34,947
But you can also send out these blessings, the normal

99
00:54:35,231 --> 00:54:39,318
Neta blessings, may you be safe, well and happy.

100
00:54:39,619 --> 00:54:41,242
May you be safe, well and happy.

101
00:54:42,143 --> 00:54:45,851
May you live contented in harmony with the world.

102
00:54:48,836 --> 00:54:57,391
Karaniangatakusalena, yantang santang padangabhisameca.

103
00:54:58,081 --> 00:55:24,543
Sākhojūcā, Suhujūcā, Suvācchocā, Sāmudhu, Anathīmāni, Sāntu Sākhojā, Subhārojā, Apākīcocā, Sāllāhu, Kāvuti, Sāntindriyocā, Nīpākojā, Apākābhokuleśu, Anānugīdo,

104
00:55:25,469 --> 00:55:55,257
Nācākūdāṃ sāmbhācārekeñci ye nāvinupāre upavādeyam sukhinavākemi nohantu sābe satāpavāntu sukhitātā ye keci panabhūtati tasavātavārava anāvasesa dhīgāvā ye mahantavā

105
00:55:55,556 --> 00:55:59,922
Ajima rasa ka nukatula.

106
00:55:59,943 --> 00:56:07,273
Dita wa ye wa adita ye chadure wa santia widure.

107
00:56:08,155 --> 00:56:15,385
Buta wa sambhawesi wa sabhe satabhavan tusukita ta.

108
00:56:16,465 --> 00:56:23,556
Naparo parang niku beta nati manyata kata chilenkenche.

109
00:56:24,869 --> 00:56:52,817
Byarosana pathigasanya Nanyamanyasadukangiceya Matayataniyamputanga Yusaykaputangandurake Ewampisababutesu Manasambhavayeaparimanam Metenjasabalukasmin

110
00:56:53,016 --> 00:57:22,820
Manasambhava Yaya Parimanam Udanga Docha Thiriyanca Asampatanga Verangasapatam Titancharan Nisinova Sayanova Yavadasa Vigatamido Eitan Satinaditya Brahmangetang Viharangitamahu

111
00:57:23,661 --> 00:57:45,103
May all beings be happy.

112
00:57:46,125 --> 00:57:51,610
Sabe sakta sukita hantu

113
00:57:52,282 --> 00:58:09,025
Very good.

114
00:58:09,085 --> 00:58:16,114
Thank you very much.

115
00:58:16,715 --> 00:58:20,461
You might be interested to know that 64 of us were there.

116
00:58:20,541 --> 00:58:22,204
Well, with me, that's 65, isn't it?

117
00:58:22,606 --> 00:58:24,429
practicing meditation together.

118
00:58:24,449 --> 00:58:25,411
How wonderful is that?

119
00:58:26,273 --> 00:58:32,023
So I don't forget from now until you fall asleep is also part of your practice, our practice, don't forget myself.

120
00:58:32,985 --> 00:58:36,911
And it's good to put something beautiful in the mind so you sleep more peacefully.

121
00:58:36,952 --> 00:58:47,230
If it's the meta, remember, make it very simple, just a blessing to yourself, to somebody you have little problems with, and to all beings.

122
00:58:47,512 --> 00:58:59,614
and you can also just put the attention on the breath, but not to investigate, that might wake you up, but just to feel this gentle waving motion wafting you into deep sleep.

123
00:58:59,635 --> 00:59:01,438
May you have a peaceful night.

